Special Assistant to Ebonyi State Government on Infrastructural Development for Concession and Road Maintenance, Frank Ngwu, said Governor David Umahi would transform Nigeria the way he is doing in Ebonyi if elected President of Nigeria in 2023. According to Ngwu, Umahi has used the lean resources available to develop Ebonyi State to an enviable height and will perform wonders if he becomes President of Nigeria. He called on Nigerians to support Umahi’s 2023 presidential ambition so that Nigeria would receive the desired transformation. -Advertisement- Ngwu, who is the supervising engineer at the ongoing Muhammadu Buhari Airport project at Onueke, Ebonyi State, stated this in Abakaliki after he was honoured as an Astute Engineer by the Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ), Correspondents’ Chapel, Ebonyi State, to mark her 2022 Press Week. He explained that Umahi had not only reduced the cost of project implementation in the state from what it used to be, but had introduced quali